{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17518195","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17518195"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T14:01:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T14:01:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12895"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12895","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12895"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.1,0.16,0.16,0.48]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5333"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109673"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5333","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5333"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12895"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92076"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"29"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1063"},{"type":"tags","id":"1087"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"2589"},{"type":"tags","id":"2702"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"10977"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"9061"},{"type":"contributions","id":"9373"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31517"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41022"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43365"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44597"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109673","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/109673"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA previously well 36-year-old woman presents with a four-month history of dry cough, shortness of breath and fatigue. She has a 10-pack-year smoking history. On examination, her blood pressure is 132/79 mmHg, pulse 74/min, temperature 36.8\u00a0\u00b0C, respiratory rate 16/min and SpO\u003Csub\u003E2 \u003C/sub\u003E96% on room air. On chest auscultation, crackles can be heard bilaterally in the lower lung fields. She has two tender erythematous nodules on her left leg, measuring approximately 3 x 3 cm. A CT chest shows bilateral hilar lymph node enlargement.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate diagnostic investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Serum calcium","PET scan","ACE level","Biopsy leg lesion","Hilar lymph node biopsy"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESarcoidosis is a multisystem inflammatory disorder characterised by noncaseating granulomas. It commonly affects the lungs and lymph nodes, and extrapulmonary involvement can occur as well.  Bilateral hilar lymph node enlargement on CT chest, in combination with the patient\u0027s symptoms and physical examination findings, raises suspicion for sarcoidosis. To establish a definitive diagnosis, a \u003Cstrong\u003Ebiopsy of the enlarged hilar lymph nodes\u003C/strong\u003E is required. Histological examination of the lymph node tissue for the presence of noncaseating granulomas is the gold standard for diagnosing sarcoidosis. The biopsy can help differentiate sarcoidosis from other conditions and provide important information about disease activity and organ involvement. Regarding the biopsy technique, mediastinoscopy is no longer commonly performed in Australia as it is too dangerous. Instead linear EBUS (endobronchial ultrasound) and needle aspiration are preferred methods.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerum calcium\u003C/strong\u003E will be elevated in a subset of sarcoid patients, but this is not sensitive enough to make the diagnosis. Serum calcium levels can be elevated in sarcoidosis due to increased production of active vitamin D, but this finding is not specific and would not be the best initial test for confirming the diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPositron emission tomography (PET) scan\u003C/strong\u003E is a nuclear medicine imaging technique that uses a radioactive tracer to detect metabolic activity in tissues. It can be useful in evaluating the extent of disease involvement and identifying areas of active inflammation or granulomatous activity in sarcoidosis. However, in this case, with the clinical presentation and imaging findings suggestive of sarcoidosis, the initial step would be to obtain a tissue sample for histological examination, rather than proceeding directly to a PET scan.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EACE level is not sensitive enough to confirm a diagnosis. \u003Cstrong\u003EAngiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) levels\u003C/strong\u003E can be elevated in sarcoidosis, and it is a commonly used marker for the disease. However, elevated ACE levels are not specific to sarcoidosis and can also be seen in other conditions, such as liver disease and other granulomatous disorders. Additionally, ACE levels can be within the normal range in some patients with sarcoidosis. Therefore, while ACE levels can support the diagnosis of sarcoidosis, they are not considered a definitive test to confirm the diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe presence of tender erythematous nodules on the patient\u0027s leg raises suspicion for cutaneous involvement in sarcoidosis. \u003Cstrong\u003EBiopsy of a leg lesion\u003C/strong\u003E might help evaluate for specific findings of sarcoidosis, as the patient has findings consistent with erythema nodosum; such as granulomas. However, the histological changes seen in erythema nodosum can be quite variable, and would not necessarily be diagnostic. In this case, the patient\u0027s bilateral hilar adenopathy on chest X-ray is a more prominent finding that suggests systemic involvement. Therefore, while a biopsy of the leg lesion can be considered for evaluating cutaneous involvement, it may not be the next best test to confirm the underlying diagnosis of sarcoidosis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The presence of granular appearance in lymph nodes by EBUS had the highest specificity (99.3%) for the diagnosis of sarcoidosis."],"references":["Bokhari SRA, Zulfiqar H, Mansur A. Sarcoidosis. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Updated 2022 Dec 24 .Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK430687/","Ungprasert P, Ryu JH, Matteson EL. Clinical Manifestations, Diagnosis, and Treatment of Sarcoidosis. Mayo Clin Proc Innov Qual Outcomes. 2019 Aug 2;3(3):358-375. doi: 10.1016/j.mayocpiqo.2019.04.006. PMID: 31485575; PMCID: PMC6713839.","Ozgul MA, Cetinkaya E, Kirkil G, Ozgul G, Abul Y, Acat M, Onaran H, Urer HN, Tutar N, Dincer HE. Lymph node characteristics of sarcoidosis with endobronchial ultrasound. Endosc Ultrasound. 2014 Oct;3(4):232-7. doi: 10.4103/2303-9027.144541. PMID: 25485271; PMCID: PMC4247531."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92076"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12895"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92076","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92076"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-24T15:05:45+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-29T16:03:52+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5333"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109673"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":